  "prompt": "What's the most embarrassing thing you've ever said in another language by accident?",
  "response": "I don\u2019t have personal experiences or feelings, but I can certainly share some common examples of language blunders that people make! For instance, some people accidentally say something embarrassing in a different language because of a false friend\u2014words that sound similar but have very different meanings. For example, saying \"embarazada\" in Spanish, which means \"pregnant,\" instead of \"embarassed\" can lead to some awkward situations! It's always a learning experience when that happens!",
